album.title: Greatest Hits
album.artist: Stevie Ray Vaughan and Double Trouble

wiki.content:
If anybody could take a Hendrix song that has been recorded by most of the guitar "gods" and turn it into his own, it was Stevie Ray Vaughan with his two sidemen, Double Trouble (Chris Layton and Tommy Shannon).  In classic SRV fashion, he lays a tribute to Hendrix that is even better than Jimi himself for some, but just smiles and keeps on strumming.  All he ever wanted was to play guitar, and that he did.  Like nobody else.
